Anterior Exterior panel. This panel has a zipper inserted on
the top witch will create access to the anterior pocket. PALS
webbing on the exterior face of the panel, it is partly
intended to help make the panel more rigid, so it might not

Superior Intermediate panel
Inferior Intermediate Panel
Sewing order:
- Prepare the three main panels individually
- anterior panel
- posterior panel
- intermediate panel
Intermediate Panel:
- Prepare Superior Section of Intermediate Panel:
- Insert zipper into Superior section.
- Bartack the zipper pull tabs at the short end of the section
- Make relief cuts in the seam allowance for 90 degree turns
- Prepare Inferior section of Intermediate panel:
- Make relief cuts in the seam allowance for 90 degree turns
- Assemble the Intermediate panel by sewing the Superior and Inferior section
together at the short edges to make a loop.
- Be exact in your measurements
- The loop length must match the circumference of the posterior and anterior
panels
- measured circumference along stich-line, not along edge of the fabric
Anterior Panel:
- Prepare the Anterior panel exterior pocket:
- bar tack PALS webbing
- insert anterior panel exterior pocket zipper
- Prepare the anterior panel interior pocket:
- finish the superior edge of the interior pocket
- Bartack the narrow elastic to the wide elastic to make organizer loops
- Sew the elastic assmebly to the interior pocket section
- Sew the interior pocket section & elastic assembly to the internal face of
- add internal webbing loop where desired.
Posterior Panel:
- essentially the same as the anterior, execept without an external pocket
- bartack or box-x carry harness attachments to the seam allowance
